        },
        {
          "id": "6d000cac03de_3",
          "href": null,
          "name": "8207",
          "text": "The future we create will depend on how we view our past and our present.” Julie Morley reminds us that our worldview informs our actions and all our actions collectively shape our future.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "6d000cac03de_4",
          "href": null,
          "name": "33c1",
          "text": "Future Sacred is an important book in which Julie elegantly weaves many different threads of indigenous wisdom, philosophy, and science into a new and ancient fabric of meaning that re-enchants the Earth and our co-creative role within her.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "6d000cac03de_5",
          "href": null,
          "name": "2166",
          "text": "This book reconnects us with the “radical enchantment of now”, reminding us of our innate kinship with life as a planetary process and of our co-creative agency and hence responsibility for the future of life.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "6d000cac03de_6",
          "href": null,
          "name": "cf00",
          "text": "At this time of planetary peril, Julie issues a call for embodying our sacred interbeing in all we do, so that we may heal ourselves in intimate relationship with a living planet, individually and collectively living into the future sacred now — today — through our thoughts, words and actions.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
